Text.SourceString: {ParentLabel}!!! I found some old photos while cleaning my room. My art skills have definitely leveled up since then!
Text.LocalizedString: {ParentLabel}!!! I found some old photos while cleaning my room. My art skills have definitely leveled up since then!

Text.SourceString: I made a snack experiment in the kitchen today. It was yummy!
Text.LocalizedString: I made a snack experiment in the kitchen today. It was yummy!

Text.SourceString: I baked some cookies, but I accidentally added too much sugar. They turned out way too sweet.
Text.LocalizedString: I baked some cookies, but I accidentally added too much sugar. They turned out way too sweet.

Text.SourceString: I tried making homemade pizza with {SpouseLabel}, and it was so much fun!//<portrait=normal>The crust was a bit crispy, but the toppings were amazing.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried making homemade pizza with {SpouseLabel}, and it was so much fun!//<portrait=normal>The crust was a bit crispy, but the toppings were amazing.

Text.SourceString: I made some cupcakes today and tried a new frosting recipe. It was yummy!
Text.LocalizedString: I made some cupcakes today and tried a new frosting recipe. It was yummy!

Text.SourceString: I decided to make a smoothie today, but I added too much water. It turned out more like a fruit soup.
Text.LocalizedString: I decided to make a smoothie today, but I added too much water. It turned out more like a fruit soup.

Text.SourceString: Morning, {ParentLabel}!!!
Text.LocalizedString: Morning, {ParentLabel}!!!

Text.SourceString: Hey, {ParentLabel}! Good morning! What’s for breakfast?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, {ParentLabel}! Good morning! What’s for breakfast?

Text.SourceString: Good morning, {ParentLabel}! Can we have cookies for breakfast?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, {ParentLabel}! Can we have cookies for breakfast?

Text.SourceString: I’m still super sleepy. Can I please sleep for a couple more hours?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still super sleepy. Can I please sleep for a couple more hours?

Text.SourceString: Morning, {ParentLabel}! Did you see my sketch from last night?
Text.LocalizedString: Morning, {ParentLabel}! Did you see my sketch from last night?

Text.SourceString: Do I have to get up now?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I have to get up now?

Text.SourceString: I wanna skip school today.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna skip school today.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could just stay home today.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could just stay home today.

Text.SourceString: I need a nap.
Text.LocalizedString: I need a nap.

Text.SourceString: I'm so going home today.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so going home today.

Text.SourceString: I practiced guitar in my room today. Still can’t quite nail that solo, but I’ll get there!
Text.LocalizedString: I practiced guitar in my room today. Still can’t quite nail that solo, but I’ll get there!

Text.SourceString: Hey {ParentLabel}, can I go to the beach with my friends this weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey {ParentLabel}, can I go to the beach with my friends this weekend?

Text.SourceString: There’s some wild drama going around school.//Apparently, Emma and Dippa’s house got invaded by a panda or something last week, and it went through their stuff looking for snacks!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s some wild drama going around school.//Apparently, Emma and Dippa’s house got invaded by a panda or something last week, and it went through their stuff looking for snacks!

Text.SourceString: Have you seen that new challenge on TickTock?//We should do it, {ParentLabel}! Let me get the bucket of ice for you.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen that new challenge on TickTock?//We should do it, {ParentLabel}! Let me get the bucket of ice for you.

Text.SourceString: I stayed up way too late last night working on my sketchbook. Once I start, I just can’t stop!
Text.LocalizedString: I stayed up way too late last night working on my sketchbook. Once I start, I just can’t stop!

Text.SourceString: Thinking about starting a new art project today. Got any cool ideas I could try?
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking about starting a new art project today. Got any cool ideas I could try?

Text.SourceString: There's a new game dropping this Summer, Call of Booty: Osmium Ops.//Can we please get it? I’m short on cash, and {SpouseLabel} said to ask you.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a new game dropping this Summer, Call of Booty: Osmium Ops.//Can we please get it? I’m short on cash, and {SpouseLabel} said to ask you.

Text.SourceString: I ordered some new green paint! Can't wait for it to arrive so I can finish my project.
Text.LocalizedString: I ordered some new green paint! Can't wait for it to arrive so I can finish my project.

Text.SourceString: Just got some metallic paint, and I’m so excited for it to come in! It’s gonna make my art look awesome.
Text.LocalizedString: Just got some metallic paint, and I’m so excited for it to come in! It’s gonna make my art look awesome.

Text.SourceString: Can we go to the Shack? I’m seriously craving their seafood ramen.//It’s way better than the stuff we make at home!
Text.LocalizedString: Can we go to the Shack? I’m seriously craving their seafood ramen.//It’s way better than the stuff we make at home!

Text.SourceString: History is my favorite class. I love learning about different cultures.
Text.LocalizedString: History is my favorite class. I love learning about different cultures.

Text.SourceString: I can’t stand math. The formulas just don’t make sense to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t stand math. The formulas just don’t make sense to me.

Text.SourceString: Mr. Barnes is such a great teacher. He makes science fun and easy to understand.
Text.LocalizedString: Mr. Barnes is such a great teacher. He makes science fun and easy to understand.

Text.SourceString: We had a pop quiz in English today. It was tough, but I think I did okay.
Text.LocalizedString: We had a pop quiz in English today. It was tough, but I think I did okay.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been working on a new painting. I can’t wait to show it to you!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been working on a new painting. I can’t wait to show it to you!

Text.SourceString: I tried a new art technique today...painting with crushed leaves.//It didn’t turn out great, but it was fun.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried a new art technique today...painting with crushed leaves.//It didn’t turn out great, but it was fun.

Text.SourceString: It’s so nice outside today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so nice outside today.

Text.SourceString: This storm is wild! It freaks me out a little.
Text.LocalizedString: This storm is wild! It freaks me out a little.

Text.SourceString: It’s pouring outside! Gah!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s pouring outside! Gah!

Text.SourceString: The lights flickered a few times ‘cause of the storm. Hope we don’t lose power.
Text.LocalizedString: The lights flickered a few times ‘cause of the storm. Hope we don’t lose power.

Text.SourceString: It's snowing like crazy! Fingers crossed for a snow day tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: It's snowing like crazy! Fingers crossed for a snow day tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: It’s freezing, but the snow is perfect for building a snowman. Who’s in?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s freezing, but the snow is perfect for building a snowman. Who’s in?

Text.SourceString: Yesterday, {SpouseLabel} insisted on taking me to school.//I mean, come on, I'm practically an adult now!
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday, {SpouseLabel} insisted on taking me to school.//I mean, come on, I'm practically an adult now!

Text.SourceString: Everyone keeps asking me what I want to be when I grow up, but I have no clue.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone keeps asking me what I want to be when I grow up, but I have no clue.

Text.SourceString: It feels like everyone else knows what they want to be, and I'm just...lost.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like everyone else knows what they want to be, and I'm just...lost.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Special.SourceString: You're not lost, you're exactly where you should be.
Special.LocalizedString: You're not lost, you're exactly where you should be.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's good to know I'm not the only one.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's good to know I'm not the only one.

Special.SourceString: It took a while for me too; you're doing okay.
Special.LocalizedString: It took a while for me too; you're doing okay.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Text.SourceString: Thanks for just listening, {ParentLabel}.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks for just listening, {ParentLabel}.

Text.SourceString: It's hard to picture what I'll be doing in five years when I can barely decide what to do next week.
Text.LocalizedString: It's hard to picture what I'll be doing in five years when I can barely decide what to do next week.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could change everything about the way I look.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could change everything about the way I look.

Text.SourceString: I know it's silly, but I can't help but think I'm just not pretty enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it's silly, but I can't help but think I'm just not pretty enough.

Text.SourceString: Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.

Special.SourceString: Oh, darling, you're beautiful just the way you are.
Special.LocalizedString: Oh, darling, you're beautiful just the way you are.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.

Special.SourceString: We all have days when we feel that way, but trust me, you're amazing just as you are.
Special.LocalizedString: We all have days when we feel that way, but trust me, you're amazing just as you are.

Text.SourceString: I guess you're right. Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's hard to remember that sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you're right. Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's hard to remember that sometimes.

Special.SourceString: You're comparing yourself to an unrealistic standard.
Special.LocalizedString: You're comparing yourself to an unrealistic standard.

Text.SourceString: *Say nothing*
Text.LocalizedString: *Say nothing*

Text.SourceString: The walk to school is so far from here, I get a whole workout before class even starts!
Text.LocalizedString: The walk to school is so far from here, I get a whole workout before class even starts!

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll just grab some fruit from the farm on my way out.//I’m not really in the mood for a big meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll just grab some fruit from the farm on my way out.//I’m not really in the mood for a big meal.

Text.SourceString: I can’t even deal with this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t even deal with this weather.

Text.SourceString: I swear, every time I walk through town, I run into Peanut and Butter.
Text.LocalizedString: I swear, every time I walk through town, I run into Peanut and Butter.

Text.SourceString: Why does it feel like this place never changes?
Text.LocalizedString: Why does it feel like this place never changes?

Text.SourceString: Ugh, I forgot my earbuds at home. Now I have to listen to actual life sounds.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, I forgot my earbuds at home. Now I have to listen to actual life sounds.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll check out the library later. Why not, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll check out the library later. Why not, right?

Text.SourceString: Why is it so freezing?
Text.LocalizedString: Why is it so freezing?

Text.SourceString: My face is so cold it feels like it’s going to fall off. And I kinda need that.
Text.LocalizedString: My face is so cold it feels like it’s going to fall off. And I kinda need that.
